# Cursor Rule: Enum Naming Convention

## Rule
All PHP enum files must end with `Enum.php` and their class names must end with `Enum`.

## Error Message
"Enum files must end with 'Enum.php' and their class names must end with 'Enum'"

## Examples

### Valid Patterns
- `app/Enums/UserTypeEnum.php`
- `modules/ModuleName/app/Enums/AppointmentStatusEnum.php`

### Invalid Patterns
- `app/Enums/UserType.php` (missing Enum suffix)
- `app/Models/Enums/UserType.php` (wrong location)

## Implementation
```php
// Correct
namespace App\Enums;

enum UserTypeEnum: string
{
    case ADMIN = 'admin';
    case PATIENT = 'patient';
}

// Incorrect
class UserType {}
```

## Auto-fix
When this rule is violated, suggest renaming the file and class to include the `Enum` suffix.

